{
  "stem": "10283.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my mother was always the shaker and doer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she went from embassy to embassy, to Lebanon to wherever.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And different countries.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father, I must say, did not want to come to America.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because my mother always had said, she can go on the tourist visa on a trip to America and try to find an affidavit.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she would have found one, because my mother was a very efficient and energetic woman.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But he said no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He does not want to go to America for some reason.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And well, times were very bad at that time in America.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he knew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And these people from Stanley Works said no, they will not give-- they don't employ Jews in America.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they will send money anywhere in the world to help us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because the director from the German firm, which Stanley had written to them and implored them to help us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He said, they will send money anywhere in the world, but they will not give affidavits and-- or give him a job in-- in-- in Massachusetts, where the factory is.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] after [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] different tries to get visas, I think, my mother-- they had friends who had already immigrated to South America, I think, to Uruguay or-- I think Uruguay.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they had written, they can get us a visa if we-- if we send $200 in dollars.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this director did wire the $200.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he wired them to Arthur Blachmann.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, Arthur Blachmann was sitting in Breslau, and this money could never be paid out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So, you know, at this time, things didn't move as quickly as today.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So by the time that was written out, it was too late.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So finally, we had this cousin, [NON-ENGLISH], in Cuba.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she wrote that she can get visas for us if we send the money.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So then they did the right-- they sent the money to her address, and she supposedly got us visas, but only for my parents and me, and my-- not for my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we decided that at this point, we are not-- we cannot help it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We're going to leave the grandparents back in Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my mother-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and we got passage on the Saint Louis from the Hamburg America line for the 13th of May in 1939.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But that was from November the until May it took to get all this straightened out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the meantime, we had moved to a very small place [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] and sold a lot of our belongings and just kept what we were going to take along.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we packed [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] what they called a lift.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were just great big wooden crates, but heavy-- heavier than crates.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were in [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] square.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were like-- like closets today.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we packed everything in there that we were allowed to take in the meantime.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Before that, we had to bring all the jewelry and all the silver and everything to a certain place to give to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were allowed two settings a person to take along, that's all, two silver settings.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And while we were packing, an official from the government came to the house to watch that we didn't put anything into this-- into this lift other than household goods and dishes and things like that.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I have to tell you also that when they bought these tickets on the Saint Louis, the line, the Hamburg America line, asked already for return tickets.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they had already an inkling that this ship will not be able to land.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Or in any event, they wanted the money for-- for both-- for both ways.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they were so glad that they got even a passage, that they got this cabin on the ship, that they took what they could, and they paid-- paid that and never even thought much about that.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So it was a terrible scene that I will never forget when we left our grandparents, you know, especially my mother's mother screamed like terrible.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But we left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we went to Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we got on the boat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was only 16 at this time, so I didn't take it so terribly you know, hard.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was with my parents, and it was an ocean voyage, my first ocean voyage.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother had made a long party dress for me, and I was learning how to dance no the ship.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I-- you know, before that, in Germany, I belonged to the [?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Vakloid, ?] I belonged to the Zionist youth group.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
